      nativeForm: 'If the past is always interpreted from the standpoint of the present — and this much seems undeniable — it follows that historical understanding is permanently provisional: not because truth is beyond our reach, but because our access to it is always mediated by the conceptual frameworks, institutional arrangements, and political investments of the moment from which we look back.',
